SIR ALEX Ferguson is to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donation" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donation" target="_blank">donate</a> &pound5000 to a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fundraising" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fundraising" target="_blank">fund</a> to build a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Statue" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Statue" target="_blank">statue</a> of a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woman" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woman" target="_blank">woman</a> who successfully led <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rent_%28musical%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rent_%28musical%29" target="_blank">rent</a> strikes during the First World WarThe former <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_United_F.C." title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_United_F.C." target="_blank">Manchester United</a> manager is supporting the Remember Mary Barbour <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fundraising" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fundraising" target="_blank">Fund</a> in memory of the âformidable firebrandâ from <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Govan" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Govan" target="_blank">Govan</a> in GlasgowMs Barbour led the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rent_%28musical%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rent_%28musical%29" target="_blank">rent</a> strikes in the city in 1915 forcing a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Menopause" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Menopause" target="_blank">change</a> in the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law" target="_blank">law</a> with the introduction of the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rent_%28musical%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rent_%28musical%29" target="_blank">Rent</a> Restrictions ActAfter the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warwickshire" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warwickshire" target="_blank">war</a> she maintained her vision and determination to deliver better conditions for women and children across the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/City_of_London" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/City_of_London" target="_blank">city</a> by blazing a trail becoming one of the first <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Female" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Female" target="_blank">female</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Councillor" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Councillor" target="_blank">councillors</a> the first <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Female" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Female" target="_blank">female</a> Baillie  a civic <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Officer_%28armed_forces%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Officer_%28armed_forces%29" target="_blank">officer</a>  and a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Female" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Female" target="_blank">female</a> magistrateSir <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Ferguson" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Ferguson" target="_blank">Alex</a> said âI take great pride in coming from <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Govan" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Govan" target="_blank">Govan</a> It's a place where I grew up learning the value of hard <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Political_corruption" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Political_corruption" target="_blank">graft</a> resolve and resilienceâMary Barbour is also from <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Govan" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Govan" target="_blank">Govan</a> and possessed all these attributes She successfully mobilised <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" target="_blank">people</a> from far and wide to take <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_action" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_action" target="_blank">direct action</a> against social injustice and changed the law of the landâA formidable firebrand she was courageous and compassionate in equal measureâI'm delighted at this opportunity to pay my respects to Mary Barbour with my &pound5000 <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donation" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donation" target="_blank">donation</a> to the Remember Mary Barbour <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fundraising" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fundraising" target="_blank">Fund</a>âThe <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_football" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_football" target="_blank">football</a> legend will meet <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" target="_blank">Glasgow</a>'s <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Provost" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Provost" target="_blank">Lord Provost</a> Sadie Docherty who launched the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fundraising" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fundraising" target="_blank">fund</a> and former MP Maria Fyfe <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Professor" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Professor" target="_blank">chair</a> of the Remember Mary Barbour Association at the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/City_of_London" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/City_of_London" target="_blank">City</a> ChambersThe <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Provost" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Provost" target="_blank">Lord Provost</a> said âIt's a pleasure to welcome <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Ferguson" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Ferguson" target="_blank">Sir Alex Ferguson</a> to the City ChambersâWe're delighted at his <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Support_group" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Support_group" target="_blank">support</a> for the Mary Barbour <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fundraising" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fundraising" target="_blank">Fund</a> As we <a href="http://dbpedi